action: optimize
reasoning: "Q3 is 12.7x slower than DuckDB (1199ms vs 95ms) and dominates total execution time. Dictionary encoding c_mktsegment eliminates the critical I/O bottleneck with 5-10x speedup potential. Zone maps provide low-risk 2-3x speedup for Q6. Better hash function is low-hanging fruit for Q3. With 1 iteration remaining, we must aggressively target the Q3 bottleneck."
selected_recommendations[3]: 0,1,5
focus_areas[3]: Dictionary-encode c_mktsegment in Q3 to eliminate fread() I/O bottleneck (5-10x speedup),Implement zone map block skipping for Q6 l_shipdate filter (2-3x speedup),Optimize Q3 hash function to reduce collisions (5-10% speedup)
strategy_notes: "Prioritizing Q3 optimization (12.7x gap) with dictionary encoding as the critical transformation. This requires re-ingestion but the 5-10x speedup justifies it for the final iteration. Zone maps and hash optimization are complementary low-risk improvements. If time permits during implementation, the Implementer may also consider adding SIMD optimizations from recommendations 3-4 as they don't require reingest."
notes: "Dictionary encoding is the game-changer for Q3 - DuckDB uses this technique universally for low-cardinality strings. Zone maps are standard in columnar databases (Parquet, ClickHouse) and align well with our sorted-by-date storage. The hash function improvement is a simple code change with measurable benefit."